      "content": "i get that, the history is complicated. but if u look at the end result, most of the world's most technologically advanced and economically powerful nations use these hierarchical, western-style models. doesn't that suggest there's something inherently more efficient or \"superior\" about that specific way of organizing a society if it's what leads to that kind of growth?",
